     LINUX COMMANDS

1.To make a file - touch (filename)
2.to see all thefiles - ls
3.to open a text editor- nano
4.there are total 7 text editors which can be opened by 
ctrl+alt+f1 to f7

5.to close the text editors - ctrl+alt+f8
6.to see the file content in the terminal itself - cat filename
7.to give complete access to the user - sudo chmod 777 fiename
8.to change the owner - sudo chown newownername oldusername
9.to see all your commands - history
10.to make zip file - tar -czf file.tar filename
11.to extract your file - tar -xvf file.tar
12.to clear screen - clear
13.to delete file - rm fileneme
14.to see the running processes - ps
15.to shutdown or reboot - shutdown or reboot
16.to become the root user - sudo -i
17.to install a file - apt-get install "name"
18.to uninstall a neew file - apt -get purge "name"
19.to update linux- sudo apt-get update 
